1
00:02:00,560 --> 00:02:02,440
Eliminate Thatri.

2
00:02:02,520 --> 00:02:04,040
If we let him live,

3
00:02:04,120 --> 00:02:06,080
he'll end up being the death of me.

4
00:02:06,160 --> 00:02:07,840
You think you're so good, Thatri?

5
00:02:10,199 --> 00:02:11,520
Mr. Thatri and Miss Rajit

6
00:02:11,600 --> 00:02:13,360
have been kidnapped by Zhang Gong Cheng.

7
00:02:13,440 --> 00:02:16,520
Please let those two vanish forever.

8
00:02:16,600 --> 00:02:17,880
May they never find their way back.

9
00:02:19,880 --> 00:02:21,320
Let's go, Rajit. Jump!

10
00:02:25,440 --> 00:02:27,800
Dear gods and spirits of the heavens,

11
00:02:27,880 --> 00:02:29,000
please be patient.

12
00:02:29,080 --> 00:02:31,040
I promise I'll finish this.

13
00:02:31,120 --> 00:02:32,120
Rajit.

14
00:02:32,960 --> 00:02:36,280
As for the wicked,
heaven never takes their side.

15
00:02:46,360 --> 00:02:48,080
I thought you'd have trouble sleeping.

16
00:02:48,760 --> 00:02:49,960
You're even snoring.

17
00:03:02,960 --> 00:03:04,280
<i>What about your comfort?</i>

18
00:03:04,360 --> 00:03:06,080
<i>My comfort?</i>

19
00:03:06,960 --> 00:03:09,680
You know, being comforted

20
00:03:09,760 --> 00:03:12,080
by the fact that
even if you end up on an island,

21
00:03:12,680 --> 00:03:14,560
you still have me right by your side.

22
00:04:05,240 --> 00:04:06,840
Get a grip, Thatri.

23
00:04:46,720 --> 00:04:48,200
- You're up early.
- You're up early.

24
00:04:56,000 --> 00:04:57,920
The food looks really delicious.

25
00:04:59,960 --> 00:05:03,440
Yeah. You should join me then.

26
00:05:04,520 --> 00:05:05,760
Okay.

27
00:05:08,960 --> 00:05:10,000
Thanks.

28
00:05:21,880 --> 00:05:23,960
You first, Uncle Ree.

29
00:05:25,560 --> 00:05:27,040
No, you first.

30
00:05:29,840 --> 00:05:30,760
Thank you.

31
00:05:44,440 --> 00:05:47,200
Mr. Thatri, someone's here to see you.

32
00:06:01,000 --> 00:06:02,720
Did you miss me, Tri?

33
00:06:03,480 --> 00:06:04,320
Srichan?

34
00:06:15,160 --> 00:06:16,880
It might not look all that luxurious,

35
00:06:16,960 --> 00:06:20,000
and the taste doesn't quite match
the Bangkok elites,

36
00:06:20,600 --> 00:06:23,080
but it's clear you're filthy rich.

37
00:06:26,480 --> 00:06:28,160
Congratulations, Tri.

38
00:06:29,600 --> 00:06:30,480
Thanks.

39
00:06:33,480 --> 00:06:34,760
And you are?

40
00:06:34,840 --> 00:06:36,160
Srichan.

41
00:06:37,760 --> 00:06:40,920
Are you a friend of Uncle Ree's
from back when he lived in Bangkok?

42
00:06:44,600 --> 00:06:46,200
Definitely not friends.

43
00:06:51,840 --> 00:06:53,240
We were lovers.

44
00:06:58,600 --> 00:07:01,640
That's not true. Well, we used to date.

45
00:07:01,720 --> 00:07:03,560
But now we are just friends.

46
00:07:05,480 --> 00:07:06,320
Just friends.

47
00:07:06,960 --> 00:07:07,840
That's right.

48
00:07:07,920 --> 00:07:10,600
We were deeply in love
back when we were in Eng--

49
00:07:17,880 --> 00:07:19,960
Henri Dunant.

50
00:07:20,920 --> 00:07:22,680
Henri Dunant Road, I mean.

51
00:07:22,760 --> 00:07:25,360
Tri used to work around that area.

52
00:07:30,080 --> 00:07:32,560
Tri, what about your friend who got hurt?

53
00:07:32,640 --> 00:07:35,680
How is he doing,
and when is he leaving the hospital?

54
00:07:40,040 --> 00:07:41,760
You don't actually have to answer me.

55
00:07:41,840 --> 00:07:43,200
I was just making small talk.

56
00:07:43,280 --> 00:07:44,400
I don't really care to know.

57
00:07:47,280 --> 00:07:50,640
Well then, please make yourself at home.

58
00:07:51,280 --> 00:07:52,880
If you'll excuse me.

59
00:08:02,560 --> 00:08:06,000
Sri, I shared everything with you

60
00:08:06,080 --> 00:08:07,600
not so you could blackmail me.

61
00:08:08,960 --> 00:08:11,360
Oh, come on. I was just teasing you.

62
00:08:11,440 --> 00:08:12,840
You take things too seriously.

63
00:08:13,920 --> 00:08:15,800
I'm aware it's a secret.

64
00:08:15,880 --> 00:08:17,400
I won't ruin your job.

65
00:08:21,960 --> 00:08:22,960
But seriously,

66
00:08:23,840 --> 00:08:27,080
your friend's niece
is absolutely gorgeous.

67
00:08:27,840 --> 00:08:31,120
No wonder you're going
all out to help her.

68
00:08:33,799 --> 00:08:35,320
She is my friend's niece.

69
00:08:36,720 --> 00:08:39,159
But you, what are you
even doing here in Phuket?

70
00:08:39,240 --> 00:08:41,120
Won't Mr. Poj throw a massive tantrum?

71
00:08:43,159 --> 00:08:44,120
He won't be throwing any tantrums

72
00:08:44,200 --> 00:08:46,200
because my old man followed me here too.

73
00:08:46,280 --> 00:08:47,200
Huh?

74
00:08:49,360 --> 00:08:52,520
Calm down, Tri. No need to panic.

75
00:08:53,520 --> 00:08:56,120
I tricked him into believing
you were in Chiang Mai,

76
00:08:56,720 --> 00:08:59,080
so he happily
brought me to Phuket himself.

77
00:09:00,640 --> 00:09:01,840
Little does the old man know,

78
00:09:01,920 --> 00:09:03,600
he's basically

79
00:09:04,200 --> 00:09:06,800
just acted as Cupid,

80
00:09:07,400 --> 00:09:10,760
delivering me right into your arms.

81
00:09:13,520 --> 00:09:16,240
Sri, this house is full of people.

82
00:09:16,880 --> 00:09:18,400
Have some respect for me.

83
00:09:20,560 --> 00:09:21,840
Fine.

84
00:09:22,520 --> 00:09:25,080
I was about to drop
some major dirt on Kajorn,

85
00:09:26,240 --> 00:09:27,560
but forget it.

86
00:09:30,560 --> 00:09:33,240
You managed to dig something up?
What did you find out?

87
00:09:48,000 --> 00:09:48,880
Huh?

88
00:09:48,960 --> 00:09:51,200
An old flame showing up here?

89
00:09:51,280 --> 00:09:52,080
Exactly.

90
00:09:52,160 --> 00:09:54,640
She literally introduced herself
as his lover.

91
00:09:54,720 --> 00:09:57,240
I always knew Uncle Ree was a player,

92
00:09:57,320 --> 00:10:00,280
but I never expected a woman
to chase him to the house like this.

93
00:10:01,800 --> 00:10:05,240
Uncle Ree, how could you do this to me?

94
00:10:05,840 --> 00:10:06,920
What am I supposed to do?

95
00:10:07,000 --> 00:10:10,360
Hey. Stop wailing, Nareewan.

96
00:10:10,440 --> 00:10:13,600
It doesn't matter
who chased him here.

97
00:10:13,680 --> 00:10:17,120
What matters is that in the present,
Uncle Ree belongs to me.

98
00:10:17,200 --> 00:10:19,640
No one is taking him away.

99
00:10:21,360 --> 00:10:22,880
Since when did Uncle Ree become yours?

100
00:10:23,760 --> 00:10:25,880
Well, it was love at first sight
on the day we met.

101
00:10:25,960 --> 00:10:28,080
- I was dreaming about him way before--
- Hey, hey.

102
00:10:28,160 --> 00:10:29,720
Stop it right now.

103
00:10:29,800 --> 00:10:31,480
Why do you guys even want him anyway?

104
00:10:32,360 --> 00:10:33,880
He's just a womanizer.

105
00:10:33,960 --> 00:10:36,360
He must have given her some kind of hope,

106
00:10:36,440 --> 00:10:38,440
or else she wouldn't have chased him here.

107
00:10:38,520 --> 00:10:40,080
He is completely irresponsible

108
00:10:40,160 --> 00:10:41,800
and treats women's feelings like toys!

109
00:10:45,720 --> 00:10:47,320
Just friends? How dare he say that?

110
00:10:47,400 --> 00:10:48,720
What kind of friends act like that?

111
00:10:48,800 --> 00:10:50,320
Does he take me for a fool or what?

112
00:10:54,520 --> 00:10:55,640
Rajit, sweetie.

113
00:10:56,240 --> 00:10:58,920
You look way angrier
about this than the two of us.

114
00:11:08,760 --> 00:11:10,640
It's wartime. This is the best I can find.

115
00:11:12,240 --> 00:11:13,440
I totally understand.

116
00:11:20,920 --> 00:11:22,800
Can we finally talk about Kajorn?

117
00:11:29,480 --> 00:11:30,800
Tri, honey.

118
00:11:31,480 --> 00:11:34,200
Don't you think
it's getting a bit too hot in here?

119
00:11:34,800 --> 00:11:37,680
I think…

120
00:11:37,760 --> 00:11:41,680
we should go find somewhere
quiet and cool to chat instead?

121
00:11:41,760 --> 00:11:43,000
Sri…

122
00:11:49,040 --> 00:11:50,320
Fine.

123
00:11:54,760 --> 00:11:59,240
Well, Kajorn didn't actually
resign out of shame or dignity.

124
00:11:59,800 --> 00:12:03,160
He's drowning in gambling debts,
which completely ruined his job.

125
00:12:03,240 --> 00:12:06,040
His own boss verified this personally.

126
00:12:08,880 --> 00:12:10,320
Always at dens and racetracks.

127
00:12:10,400 --> 00:12:13,000
Debt collectors swarm this office daily.

128
00:12:13,080 --> 00:12:14,720
You barely touch your work.

129
00:12:14,800 --> 00:12:16,960
You've brought nothing
but shame to our department.

130
00:12:18,560 --> 00:12:20,120
I am truly sorry, sir.

131
00:12:20,200 --> 00:12:21,680
Please give me one more chance.

132
00:12:21,760 --> 00:12:22,840
I beg of you.

133
00:12:22,920 --> 00:12:24,520
I gave you so many chances.

134
00:12:24,600 --> 00:12:25,640
You failed every time.

135
00:12:26,280 --> 00:12:30,280
Enough is enough. I'm handing
this over to the disciplinary board.

136
00:12:30,360 --> 00:12:32,320
You can go make your excuses to them.

137
00:12:35,120 --> 00:12:37,600
Hey! Out of the way!

138
00:12:37,680 --> 00:12:38,800
You're in the way!

139
00:12:38,880 --> 00:12:41,240
Get out, get out! I said move!

140
00:12:41,320 --> 00:12:42,960
Move it!

141
00:12:43,040 --> 00:12:45,840
<i>But that gigolo is sharper than he looks.</i>

142
00:12:45,920 --> 00:12:47,440
<i>Lately, I heard</i>

143
00:12:47,520 --> 00:12:51,440
<i>he got with the sister of a triad boss</i>
<i>and is already planning a wedding.</i>

144
00:13:01,480 --> 00:13:02,320
Getting married?

145
00:13:04,840 --> 00:13:06,440
Why did he come back for Rajit?

146
00:13:08,480 --> 00:13:12,040
Do you know the name
of this triad boss's sister?

147
00:13:12,840 --> 00:13:15,240
Of course I do.
I didn't dig this deep for nothing.

148
00:13:15,320 --> 00:13:17,360
- Then…
- But I'm not telling.

149
00:13:22,800 --> 00:13:24,120
Have you ever considered

150
00:13:24,200 --> 00:13:27,120
what I had to sacrifice to get this intel?

151
00:13:28,920 --> 00:13:32,680
Nothing in this world comes for free.

152
00:13:37,960 --> 00:13:39,200
Good grief!

153
00:13:40,000 --> 00:13:41,280
How scandalous!

154
00:13:44,000 --> 00:13:46,240
First, Rajit brings her old flame
into this house,

155
00:13:46,320 --> 00:13:48,200
and now you bring…

156
00:13:50,120 --> 00:13:51,480
a low-class woman

157
00:13:52,080 --> 00:13:53,680
in here too?

158
00:13:55,160 --> 00:13:56,640
What do you take this house for?

159
00:13:56,720 --> 00:14:00,640
Can't shake off
your low-class habits, can you?

160
00:14:01,960 --> 00:14:02,800
Tri.

161
00:14:03,800 --> 00:14:05,360
Who is this old hag?

162
00:14:05,440 --> 00:14:07,080
She barged in and started screeching

163
00:14:07,160 --> 00:14:09,160
like a low-class street rat.

164
00:14:10,800 --> 00:14:12,040
She's ugly,

165
00:14:12,120 --> 00:14:13,360
and her attitude is even uglier.

166
00:14:14,680 --> 00:14:16,800
I should thank the heavens

167
00:14:16,880 --> 00:14:18,920
I wasn't born looking like that.

168
00:14:19,000 --> 00:14:20,040
You!

169
00:14:22,920 --> 00:14:24,280
What?

170
00:14:24,880 --> 00:14:26,000
Let me get a closer look.

171
00:14:27,520 --> 00:14:30,960
Oh dear. You're covered in wrinkles.

172
00:14:31,560 --> 00:14:33,560
That outfit might be pricey,

173
00:14:33,640 --> 00:14:35,920
but it screams zero taste.

174
00:14:37,960 --> 00:14:40,520
Well, you clearly have no style.

175
00:14:40,600 --> 00:14:43,840
Fashion reflects one's education, Auntie.

176
00:14:43,920 --> 00:14:46,600
Anyone with money can buy luxury brands.

177
00:14:47,560 --> 00:14:50,400
But taste? That requires proper education.

178
00:14:54,760 --> 00:14:55,840
You!

179
00:15:03,040 --> 00:15:04,440
Sri…

180
00:15:07,920 --> 00:15:09,600
I'm dying to see what she looks like.

181
00:15:09,680 --> 00:15:11,920
The nerve of her,
tracking Uncle Ree all the way here.

182
00:15:12,000 --> 00:15:14,040
Just wait till I catch her.

183
00:15:14,120 --> 00:15:15,760
We need to kick her back to Bangkok.

184
00:15:15,840 --> 00:15:18,080
How dare she mess with our Uncle Ree.

185
00:15:19,560 --> 00:15:21,320
I honestly don't get you two.

186
00:15:21,400 --> 00:15:23,680
What is it about Uncle Ree
that's even so special?

187
00:15:32,600 --> 00:15:34,360
Sri…

188
00:15:34,920 --> 00:15:37,640
- Tri, stay out of this!
- How dare you slap me?

189
00:15:42,040 --> 00:15:43,680
Sri, stop.

190
00:15:45,760 --> 00:15:47,320
How dare you?

191
00:15:56,960 --> 00:15:58,520
Don't get in my way!

192
00:16:07,280 --> 00:16:09,160
Stop that!

193
00:16:09,240 --> 00:16:11,080
How dare you?

194
00:16:11,760 --> 00:16:12,800
Ms. Srichan.

195
00:16:12,880 --> 00:16:15,000
Stop that!
Leave my aunt alone!

196
00:16:15,080 --> 00:16:17,000
Come on, guys,

197
00:16:17,080 --> 00:16:19,160
don't just stand there. Help me.

198
00:16:21,240 --> 00:16:23,240
Go ahead. Didn't you say
you wanted to see her?

199
00:16:26,760 --> 00:16:28,120
I have an urgent errand.

200
00:16:28,200 --> 00:16:29,400
I'm leaving.

201
00:16:29,480 --> 00:16:31,200
Wait, hold on.

202
00:16:33,800 --> 00:16:36,080
- Hey, wait for me.
- Nareewan!

203
00:16:38,600 --> 00:16:39,680
Sri.

204
00:16:39,760 --> 00:16:43,440
Stop that. Don't hurt her.

205
00:16:44,920 --> 00:16:46,400
Are you okay?

206
00:16:52,600 --> 00:16:54,120
Come on then.

207
00:16:55,480 --> 00:16:56,360
Tri.

208
00:16:56,440 --> 00:16:58,480
She started it first.

209
00:16:58,560 --> 00:17:00,160
It's okay, Auntie.

210
00:17:06,839 --> 00:17:08,200
This is all your fault.

211
00:17:08,280 --> 00:17:10,280
If she hadn't chased you here,

212
00:17:10,359 --> 00:17:12,319
this mess wouldn't have happened.

213
00:17:13,319 --> 00:17:14,520
Sri came here on her own

214
00:17:14,599 --> 00:17:16,079
and started that fight on her own.

215
00:17:16,160 --> 00:17:17,280
How is this my fault?

216
00:17:18,200 --> 00:17:19,200
I bet

217
00:17:19,280 --> 00:17:21,760
you must have given her some kind of hope.

218
00:17:21,839 --> 00:17:23,560
Why else would she come all this way?

219
00:17:24,560 --> 00:17:26,119
Stop putting words in my mouth.

220
00:17:26,200 --> 00:17:27,920
I never gave her any hope.

221
00:17:28,000 --> 00:17:29,360
And more importantly,

222
00:17:29,440 --> 00:17:31,160
Sri already has a husband.

223
00:17:31,240 --> 00:17:33,440
I'm not stupid enough
to mess with another man's wife.

224
00:17:34,800 --> 00:17:37,640
Wait, Ms. Srichan is a married woman?

225
00:17:37,720 --> 00:17:38,840
Exactly.

226
00:17:38,920 --> 00:17:41,120
But we broke up
way before she got married.

227
00:17:41,760 --> 00:17:43,640
We're just friends now.

228
00:17:45,040 --> 00:17:46,880
So even though she's a married woman,

229
00:17:46,960 --> 00:17:48,480
you still wouldn't spare her?

230
00:17:49,480 --> 00:17:51,640
Aren't you afraid
of burning in hell for adultery?

231
00:17:52,280 --> 00:17:53,680
Do you ever listen?

232
00:17:53,760 --> 00:17:55,280
I just said we are friends.

233
00:17:56,240 --> 00:17:57,920
I never expected

234
00:17:58,000 --> 00:18:00,120
you to be this kind of man, Uncle Ree.

235
00:18:06,680 --> 00:18:07,720
Women…

236
00:18:09,240 --> 00:18:13,760
DISTRICT CHIEF'S RESIDENCE

237
00:18:20,400 --> 00:18:22,040
You have a great appetite tonight.

238
00:18:23,640 --> 00:18:25,400
I got some exercise today.

239
00:18:25,480 --> 00:18:28,240
So I'm feeling quite refreshed.

240
00:18:30,160 --> 00:18:31,200
The food is delicious.

241
00:18:31,280 --> 00:18:32,520
Thank you very much.

242
00:18:32,600 --> 00:18:34,960
I must thank you, District Chief,

243
00:18:35,040 --> 00:18:36,640
for generously letting us stay here.

244
00:18:37,360 --> 00:18:39,120
Things are so tight everywhere,

245
00:18:39,200 --> 00:18:41,800
yet we're here bothering you.
I really feel bad.

246
00:18:41,880 --> 00:18:42,920
Don't worry.

247
00:18:43,600 --> 00:18:45,920
The Governor instructed me
to take the utmost care of you

248
00:18:46,000 --> 00:18:47,760
and your wife.

249
00:18:47,840 --> 00:18:49,280
He was quite disappointed

250
00:18:49,360 --> 00:18:51,240
that his residence is under renovation,

251
00:18:51,320 --> 00:18:53,480
otherwise, he would have hosted you there

252
00:18:53,560 --> 00:18:55,000
and provided better care.

253
00:18:56,880 --> 00:18:59,480
Well, my wife and I

254
00:18:59,560 --> 00:19:01,560
plan to travel around Phuket
for a few more days.

255
00:19:02,240 --> 00:19:04,480
Do you have any places to recommend?

256
00:19:05,680 --> 00:19:06,880
There are plenty.

257
00:19:08,080 --> 00:19:10,400
Although we're famous for tin mining,

258
00:19:11,040 --> 00:19:14,160
I find the scenery here truly beautiful.

259
00:19:16,200 --> 00:19:18,240
If you stay long enough,

260
00:19:18,320 --> 00:19:20,760
I guarantee you'll fall in love with it.

261
00:19:23,200 --> 00:19:26,080
Right after the Vegetarian Festival,
we'll have the Lantern Festival.

262
00:19:26,160 --> 00:19:28,200
The shrines and the entire town

263
00:19:28,280 --> 00:19:30,360
will be decorated with red lanterns.

264
00:19:31,360 --> 00:19:32,480
Are you interested?

265
00:19:34,120 --> 00:19:36,800
Just picturing it gets me so excited.

266
00:19:40,440 --> 00:19:42,240
Well, speaking of the festival,

267
00:19:42,320 --> 00:19:45,360
will the merchants and wealthy elites
be attending as well?

268
00:19:46,240 --> 00:19:47,080
Certainly.

269
00:19:48,680 --> 00:19:50,600
Phuket has been
in a slump for quite a while.

270
00:19:51,240 --> 00:19:52,760
So, we host a grand festival this year

271
00:19:52,840 --> 00:19:54,920
to bring some life back to the locals.

272
00:20:02,760 --> 00:20:03,720
Hey.

273
00:20:03,800 --> 00:20:05,840
Looking for business connections again?

274
00:20:06,600 --> 00:20:08,520
I thought you said
we came here for a vacation.

275
00:20:09,320 --> 00:20:13,240
It is a vacation, mostly.
Just adding a little side quest.

276
00:20:13,320 --> 00:20:15,240
Only a tiny bit, okay?

277
00:20:18,040 --> 00:20:20,480
- Let's enjoy the meal. Try this one.
- Yes, yes.

278
00:20:20,560 --> 00:20:21,400
What is it?

279
00:20:21,480 --> 00:20:23,000
Stir-fried pork with shrimp paste.

280
00:20:23,600 --> 00:20:25,480
- Stir-fried pork with shrimp paste?
- Yes, sir.

281
00:20:26,160 --> 00:20:27,680
It's our signature Southern specialty.

282
00:20:35,280 --> 00:20:37,200
Vegetarian for ten days really paid off.

283
00:20:37,280 --> 00:20:39,640
The food shortages have eased up a lot.

284
00:20:40,760 --> 00:20:41,880
Right.

285
00:20:46,720 --> 00:20:49,280
With shipments finally arriving,

286
00:20:49,360 --> 00:20:51,440
the situation in Phuket
should lighten up a lot.

287
00:20:53,680 --> 00:20:54,520
Sure.

288
00:20:57,880 --> 00:20:58,880
What's wrong with you?

289
00:21:00,160 --> 00:21:01,280
Nothing is wrong.

290
00:21:01,360 --> 00:21:02,480
Then there definitely is.

291
00:21:03,040 --> 00:21:05,240
Every time a woman says that,
it always ends in chaos.

292
00:21:08,040 --> 00:21:10,960
You seem to understand
women so well, Uncle Ree.

293
00:21:11,960 --> 00:21:15,800
No wonder Ms. Srichan has been staying
in Phuket for ten whole days

294
00:21:15,880 --> 00:21:17,320
without any sign of leaving.

295
00:21:17,920 --> 00:21:19,000
You're mad about that?

296
00:21:19,920 --> 00:21:20,960
Mad?

297
00:21:21,880 --> 00:21:23,080
Why would I be mad?

298
00:21:23,160 --> 00:21:25,720
What is there for me to be upset about?

299
00:21:27,040 --> 00:21:30,000
Anyway, there are no issues
with the accounts, right?

300
00:21:31,960 --> 00:21:33,480
Then I'll be taking my leave.

301
00:21:50,880 --> 00:21:53,320
Getting involved with a married woman.

302
00:21:56,280 --> 00:21:58,400
How can he be such a shameless man?

303
00:22:12,800 --> 00:22:13,640
- Miss Rajit.
- Rajit.

304
00:22:15,680 --> 00:22:17,200
- I came to ask--
- Would you--

305
00:22:19,480 --> 00:22:21,800
Please, one at a time.

306
00:22:23,280 --> 00:22:24,920
Mr. Vijarn, what is it?

307
00:22:26,480 --> 00:22:29,800
Well, I was hoping to invite you

308
00:22:29,880 --> 00:22:32,800
to come to the Lantern Festival
tonight with me.

309
00:22:36,040 --> 00:22:38,600
Hey, I was just
about to ask the same thing.

310
00:22:38,680 --> 00:22:40,280
Go with me instead.

311
00:23:00,960 --> 00:23:02,240
The Lantern Festival?

312
00:23:02,320 --> 00:23:04,280
You want to go to that event, Sri?

313
00:23:04,960 --> 00:23:07,440
Yes. What's so strange about that?

314
00:23:08,280 --> 00:23:09,960
I've been here for over ten days now.

315
00:23:10,040 --> 00:23:12,280
I'm sick of the beaches and the mountains.

316
00:23:13,280 --> 00:23:16,080
I just want to have
a relaxing stroll for once, that's all.

317
00:23:17,560 --> 00:23:18,720
But that's at night.

318
00:23:18,800 --> 00:23:20,680
Can you really sneak away from Mr. Poj?

319
00:23:22,120 --> 00:23:23,920
I have my ways.

320
00:23:24,680 --> 00:23:26,840
Besides, you've been dodging me

321
00:23:27,480 --> 00:23:29,480
all day anyway, haven't you?

322
00:23:29,560 --> 00:23:32,040
Hold on, Sri. You practically tore--

323
00:23:32,880 --> 00:23:35,160
I mean, you beat Paetai up so badly.

324
00:23:35,240 --> 00:23:37,720
I had to run around
fixing that mess for days.

325
00:23:38,520 --> 00:23:40,320
How can you say I'm avoiding you?

326
00:23:41,560 --> 00:23:44,920
I've been dying to see you
just so we can talk about Kajorn.

327
00:23:46,960 --> 00:23:49,680
Then tonight, you'll definitely
get your answers.

328
00:23:50,800 --> 00:23:53,320
As long as you do what I ask.

329
00:24:07,160 --> 00:24:09,400
Thank you very much, Mr. Poj.

330
00:24:09,480 --> 00:24:11,240
I'm truly flattered.

331
00:24:11,320 --> 00:24:13,200
You are my elder,

332
00:24:13,280 --> 00:24:14,840
yet you took the time to visit

333
00:24:14,920 --> 00:24:16,800
and even brought such a wonderful gift.

334
00:24:17,920 --> 00:24:20,160
Don't mention it,
it's just a small gesture.

335
00:24:20,240 --> 00:24:22,000
The District Chief here told me

336
00:24:22,080 --> 00:24:24,000
that the Adisuan family

337
00:24:24,080 --> 00:24:25,920
is the wealthiest in Phuket.

338
00:24:26,000 --> 00:24:28,480
I simply wanted to introduce myself,

339
00:24:28,560 --> 00:24:29,600
hoping that one day,

340
00:24:29,680 --> 00:24:32,320
I might be able
to rely on the support of the Adisuans.

341
00:24:34,280 --> 00:24:36,200
Please don't say that.

342
00:24:36,280 --> 00:24:38,120
It is a youngster like me

343
00:24:38,200 --> 00:24:41,680
who should be seeking guidance
from a nationwide tycoon like you.

344
00:24:48,120 --> 00:24:49,400
By the way, is Mr. Thatri not around?

345
00:24:53,280 --> 00:24:54,280
Are you alright, sir?

346
00:24:57,240 --> 00:25:00,600
District Chief,
who were you talking about?

347
00:25:01,440 --> 00:25:04,320
Well, Mr. Thatri, Miss Rajit's uncle.

348
00:25:05,720 --> 00:25:06,640
Is something wrong?

349
00:25:11,080 --> 00:25:12,800
No, no, it's nothing.

350
00:25:13,560 --> 00:25:15,280
People can share the same name.

351
00:25:16,520 --> 00:25:20,280
A scumbag like that guy
would never be around a place like this.

352
00:25:21,640 --> 00:25:23,200
Right?

353
00:25:32,760 --> 00:25:34,160
How the hell did he get here?

354
00:25:47,480 --> 00:25:51,640
By the way, Mr. Poj,
are you here in town on business?

355
00:25:51,720 --> 00:25:53,760
Oh, no.

356
00:25:53,840 --> 00:25:57,280
Actually, I brought my wife here
for a second honeymoon.

357
00:25:57,360 --> 00:25:58,600
That's right.

358
00:25:58,680 --> 00:26:01,200
It's just such a pity
that Sri didn't want to tag along.

359
00:26:01,280 --> 00:26:03,960
Otherwise, I'd love
to introduce her to you.

360
00:26:06,800 --> 00:26:08,520
- Sri?
- Yes.

361
00:26:08,600 --> 00:26:10,440
Would that happen to be Ms. Srichan?

362
00:26:10,520 --> 00:26:13,160
Huh? You know my wife?

363
00:26:15,560 --> 00:26:19,040
Well, I suppose that's not too surprising.
Sri is quite the socialite, after all.

364
00:26:19,120 --> 00:26:20,480
She knows a lot of people.

365
00:26:20,560 --> 00:26:21,840
Right.

366
00:26:21,920 --> 00:26:23,840
What a small world.

367
00:26:24,760 --> 00:26:27,080
- It's always good to build connections.
- Indeed.

368
00:26:35,080 --> 00:26:38,600
I thought Ms. Srichan ran away
from her husband to come here.

369
00:26:38,680 --> 00:26:41,400
But guess what?
Her husband literally came with her,

370
00:26:41,480 --> 00:26:43,600
and you're still trying to have an affair?

371
00:26:43,680 --> 00:26:45,920
Mr. Poj is sitting right there
in our house.

372
00:26:46,000 --> 00:26:47,760
What on earth is your heart made of?

373
00:26:47,840 --> 00:26:49,520
Are you not afraid of hell?

374
00:26:49,600 --> 00:26:51,320
When did I ever have an affair?

375
00:26:51,400 --> 00:26:54,040
Sri is the one causing all this chaos.
I stayed out of it.

376
00:26:54,840 --> 00:26:57,760
Oh, really? Then, where
have you been just now?

377
00:27:02,200 --> 00:27:03,800
You went to see Srichan.

378
00:27:03,880 --> 00:27:05,760
Don't you dare think I don't know.

379
00:27:05,840 --> 00:27:07,560
Stop making excuses

380
00:27:07,640 --> 00:27:10,960
before I completely lose
my respect for you.

381
00:27:12,080 --> 00:27:14,440
Whether you respect me or not,

382
00:27:14,520 --> 00:27:15,520
I couldn't care less.

383
00:27:16,120 --> 00:27:17,000
But let me tell you,

384
00:27:17,080 --> 00:27:19,560
all the trouble I'm facing right now
is entirely because of you.

385
00:27:19,640 --> 00:27:21,040
You have no right to judge me.

386
00:27:21,120 --> 00:27:22,400
That is incredibly low.

387
00:27:22,480 --> 00:27:24,600
How dare you blame me for your own mess?

388
00:27:24,680 --> 00:27:26,440
You are no gentleman.

389
00:27:48,280 --> 00:27:50,440
At first, I thought you weren't coming.

390
00:27:51,280 --> 00:27:52,760
But when I heard you changed your mind,

391
00:27:54,000 --> 00:27:55,320
I was absolutely thrilled.

392
00:27:56,200 --> 00:27:57,240
Right.

393
00:27:58,280 --> 00:28:00,600
But it would have been much more fun

394
00:28:00,680 --> 00:28:02,080
if it were just the two of us.

395
00:28:05,120 --> 00:28:06,120
No can do.

396
00:28:07,320 --> 00:28:09,440
Rajit isn't that foolish.

397
00:28:10,840 --> 00:28:12,520
You two came along as well?

398
00:28:12,600 --> 00:28:14,760
Aiya. We actually had this planned.

399
00:28:14,840 --> 00:28:16,880
Of course we had to show up.

400
00:28:18,960 --> 00:28:20,360
Come on, girls.

401
00:28:20,440 --> 00:28:22,240
I'm dying to walk around the festival now.

402
00:28:22,320 --> 00:28:25,520
It might help me forget the awful things
and awful people.

403
00:28:25,600 --> 00:28:26,920
Let's go.

404
00:28:27,000 --> 00:28:28,480
- Let's go.
- Come on.

405
00:28:46,920 --> 00:28:49,200
Oh my!

406
00:28:49,280 --> 00:28:53,000
This is as lively as the Red Cross Fair
or the Sanam Luang Festival back home.

407
00:28:53,080 --> 00:28:55,840
And this is even with the bad economy.

408
00:28:55,920 --> 00:28:58,800
Just imagine how vibrant Phuket would be
during prime economic times.

409
00:29:04,280 --> 00:29:05,640
Wonderful.

410
00:29:08,440 --> 00:29:10,160
What's wrong?

411
00:29:10,240 --> 00:29:11,800
My stomach hurts so bad.

412
00:29:12,440 --> 00:29:14,800
It has to be from the crab this evening.

413
00:29:14,880 --> 00:29:16,920
Can you hold on? Let me take you back.

414
00:29:17,000 --> 00:29:19,920
Oh. It's fine.

415
00:29:20,000 --> 00:29:21,920
I noticed a public restroom

416
00:29:22,000 --> 00:29:23,840
just over there when we walked past.

417
00:29:23,920 --> 00:29:25,520
I can just use that one.

418
00:29:26,960 --> 00:29:28,320
Are you absolutely sure?

419
00:29:28,400 --> 00:29:30,360
Yes. Just wait right here.

420
00:29:30,440 --> 00:29:31,560
Are you sure?

421
00:29:31,640 --> 00:29:33,680
I'll be right back. Ouch.

422
00:29:40,560 --> 00:29:44,240
HUANG IAM BARBERSHOP

423
00:29:45,640 --> 00:29:47,200
Tri, Tri.

424
00:29:48,200 --> 00:29:49,200
Let's get out of here, now.

425
00:29:49,280 --> 00:29:50,200
Hold on, Sri.

426
00:29:51,080 --> 00:29:51,920
Where to?

427
00:29:52,720 --> 00:29:55,400
Anywhere. Before my old man
tracks me down.

428
00:29:55,480 --> 00:29:57,920
- Let's go.
- Mr. Poj is here?

429
00:29:58,520 --> 00:29:59,880
Yes.

430
00:29:59,960 --> 00:30:02,000
You'd better tell me
about Kajorn right now.

431
00:30:02,080 --> 00:30:03,520
I'd rather not get stomped.

432
00:30:03,600 --> 00:30:06,640
No way. If I tell you now,
you'll just ditch me and run off again.

433
00:30:06,720 --> 00:30:09,360
I know you too well, Tri.

434
00:30:10,240 --> 00:30:13,120
I've already played along with you.
Just tell me, please.

435
00:30:15,000 --> 00:30:16,280
In that case,

436
00:30:16,360 --> 00:30:18,880
you have to keep me satisfied first.

437
00:30:26,760 --> 00:30:28,000
How much is this?

438
00:30:30,760 --> 00:30:32,240
Can I get a discount?

439
00:30:36,680 --> 00:30:39,600
Miss Rajit. I bought
some chive cakes for you.

440
00:30:39,680 --> 00:30:41,800
This stall is incredibly delicious.

441
00:30:41,880 --> 00:30:44,840
Rajit, let's go exploring
over that way with me?

442
00:30:48,760 --> 00:30:50,240
Let's head over that way, shall we?

443
00:30:50,320 --> 00:30:51,880
Oh, right. Let's go.

444
00:30:53,240 --> 00:30:55,840
Well, how about we go together?

445
00:30:56,880 --> 00:30:59,400
If you two want to head out together,
please be my guest.

446
00:30:59,480 --> 00:31:01,080
I can look after Miss Rajit.

447
00:31:04,680 --> 00:31:05,720
Give us just a moment.

448
00:31:07,040 --> 00:31:09,880
I told you not to come out tonight.

449
00:31:11,560 --> 00:31:13,840
I'm so sorry, guys. I swear

450
00:31:13,920 --> 00:31:16,640
I will never do something stupid
just out of spite again.

451
00:31:17,960 --> 00:31:19,280
Spite? Who are you talking about?

452
00:31:21,160 --> 00:31:22,720
Uh… Hmm?

453
00:31:28,440 --> 00:31:29,480
Mr. Poj.

454
00:31:30,080 --> 00:31:30,960
Miss Rajit.

455
00:31:32,720 --> 00:31:34,560
It's so lucky to meet you here.

456
00:31:34,640 --> 00:31:36,480
Could you tell me

457
00:31:36,560 --> 00:31:39,120
where the public restroom is?

458
00:31:39,200 --> 00:31:41,640
Oh, there aren't any public ones here.

459
00:31:41,720 --> 00:31:43,240
This is a residential area.

460
00:31:43,320 --> 00:31:44,680
If you really need to go,

461
00:31:44,760 --> 00:31:47,400
you can just ask the locals.

462
00:31:47,480 --> 00:31:48,840
Oh, really?

463
00:31:50,680 --> 00:31:53,240
By the way,
are you the one having the issue?

464
00:31:53,320 --> 00:31:55,160
Oh, it's not me.

465
00:31:55,240 --> 00:31:57,040
It's my wife.

466
00:31:57,120 --> 00:31:58,680
She was going to a public restroom,

467
00:31:58,760 --> 00:32:02,680
but she's been gone for so long now.
I'm worried about her.

468
00:32:11,120 --> 00:32:12,360
I've told you, haven't I?

469
00:32:13,040 --> 00:32:14,680
If you don't do as I say…

470
00:32:17,160 --> 00:32:18,840
you won't get anything.

471
00:32:21,640 --> 00:32:23,400
I've told you a million times,

472
00:32:23,480 --> 00:32:24,680
you're a married woman.

473
00:32:24,760 --> 00:32:26,040
This is inappropriate.

474
00:32:27,280 --> 00:32:29,560
Stop bringing
that old man up, will you?

475
00:32:29,640 --> 00:32:31,120
I don't love him.

476
00:32:31,200 --> 00:32:33,880
I only married him
because my family was completely broke.

477
00:32:34,560 --> 00:32:36,160
You didn't love me either.

478
00:32:36,760 --> 00:32:38,800
If you did, you wouldn't have
dumped me back in England.

479
00:32:38,880 --> 00:32:42,840
I was young back then.
And those foreigners were so much sexier.

480
00:32:43,440 --> 00:32:44,800
I made a mistake.

481
00:32:46,000 --> 00:32:47,280
Tri,

482
00:32:47,360 --> 00:32:49,760
just give me a chance
to make it up to you.

483
00:32:52,440 --> 00:32:54,160
But I'm poor now.

484
00:32:54,240 --> 00:32:56,080
Would you be willing to struggle with me?

485
00:33:07,480 --> 00:33:09,520
In that case, would you like us

486
00:33:09,600 --> 00:33:12,040
to help you look for Ms. Srichan?

487
00:33:12,120 --> 00:33:13,240
Really?

488
00:33:14,000 --> 00:33:15,680
Thank you so much.

489
00:33:15,760 --> 00:33:18,040
My wife is wearing a green skirt,

490
00:33:18,120 --> 00:33:20,560
black shoes, black gloves,

491
00:33:20,640 --> 00:33:21,960
and carrying a black handbag.

492
00:33:22,720 --> 00:33:24,920
But Rajit, we came here
to enjoy the festival.

493
00:33:25,000 --> 00:33:27,320
I don't feel like we've seen anything yet.

494
00:33:29,480 --> 00:33:32,120
If you're not happy,
you're welcome to leave first.

495
00:33:32,200 --> 00:33:34,160
Can't you see someone is in distress here?

496
00:33:36,560 --> 00:33:39,160
Miss Rajit, I'll gladly help you.

497
00:33:39,960 --> 00:33:41,520
Thank you so much.

498
00:33:41,600 --> 00:33:42,480
My pleasure.

499
00:33:42,560 --> 00:33:45,080
In that case, let's split up

500
00:33:45,160 --> 00:33:46,920
and regroup back here later.

501
00:33:47,000 --> 00:33:50,720
Right. Then, Rajit and I will go this way.

502
00:33:50,800 --> 00:33:53,040
And Nareewan, you go over there.

503
00:33:53,960 --> 00:33:56,520
As for the rest of you,
try checking near the shrine alleyway.

504
00:33:56,600 --> 00:33:57,440
Alright.

505
00:34:00,520 --> 00:34:01,520
Let's go.

506
00:34:10,560 --> 00:34:11,719
Damn it.

507
00:34:13,880 --> 00:34:15,719
When will I ever get a chance?

508
00:34:22,520 --> 00:34:24,440
If you still can't make up your mind,

509
00:34:25,400 --> 00:34:26,360
let's get out of here.

510
00:34:30,000 --> 00:34:32,760
forget about the money then.

511
00:34:33,560 --> 00:34:34,600
Because right now,

512
00:34:35,199 --> 00:34:37,480
we have something
way more important to do.

513
00:34:38,639 --> 00:34:39,840
Mr. Poj…

514
00:34:42,719 --> 00:34:45,199
Tri, Tri.

515
00:34:45,280 --> 00:34:46,760
Tri, where are you going?

516
00:34:57,200 --> 00:34:58,360
Uncle Ree?

517
00:35:01,200 --> 00:35:02,840
Hey! What?

518
00:35:14,280 --> 00:35:15,760
How can he run so fast?

519
00:35:15,840 --> 00:35:17,520
Tri, if I catch you…

520
00:35:30,640 --> 00:35:31,840
What's wrong with you?

521
00:35:34,640 --> 00:35:38,560
S, H, A, M, and E. That's shame.

522
00:35:39,280 --> 00:35:40,640
Do you understand the word, Uncle Ree?

523
00:35:42,240 --> 00:35:43,760
Her husband is literally here,

524
00:35:43,840 --> 00:35:45,560
and yet you two still sneak around.

525
00:35:46,160 --> 00:35:49,240
If you don't care about your dignity,
at least think of our family.

526
00:35:49,880 --> 00:35:51,360
Check the facts before you accuse me.

527
00:35:51,440 --> 00:35:53,160
If I were sleeping around with her,

528
00:35:53,240 --> 00:35:54,520
why would I run away from her?

529
00:35:54,600 --> 00:35:56,360
Did I look like I was chasing after her?

530
00:35:57,880 --> 00:35:58,840
Well…

531
00:35:58,920 --> 00:36:02,520
Then what is your excuse
for meeting up with her?

532
00:36:02,600 --> 00:36:03,960
It's all because of you.

533
00:36:05,800 --> 00:36:08,800
Because of what?
I didn't quite catch that.

534
00:36:09,640 --> 00:36:10,560
Then forget it.

535
00:36:10,640 --> 00:36:11,960
It won't kill you.

536
00:36:12,560 --> 00:36:14,560
Hey. Wait a minute.

537
00:36:14,640 --> 00:36:18,240
Running away
because you lost the argument?

538
00:36:18,320 --> 00:36:19,520
Stop right there, Uncle Ree.

539
00:36:19,600 --> 00:36:21,040
I said stop.

540
00:36:21,120 --> 00:36:24,440
Uncle Ree, if you have anything
to say for yourself, say it.

541
00:36:35,000 --> 00:36:36,360
It's stunning.

542
00:36:45,720 --> 00:36:46,720
It really is.

543
00:36:56,560 --> 00:36:58,440
ROJ SILP PHOTO STUDIO

544
00:37:02,680 --> 00:37:05,200
- Rajit.
- Yes?

545
00:37:05,880 --> 00:37:07,200
Shall we get a photo?

546
00:37:14,240 --> 00:37:15,080
Sure.

547
00:37:16,440 --> 00:37:17,360
Let's go.

548
00:37:35,960 --> 00:37:36,840
Sri.

549
00:37:38,000 --> 00:37:39,240
Poj.

550
00:37:44,440 --> 00:37:46,320
I've been searching for ages.

551
00:37:46,920 --> 00:37:48,600
I knew you'd get lost.

552
00:37:49,400 --> 00:37:50,800
Come on, let's go.

553
00:37:50,880 --> 00:37:54,120
Oh, wait. Are we leaving already?

554
00:37:54,200 --> 00:37:57,720
No, not yet. We need to inform
Miss Rajit and her friends first.

555
00:37:57,800 --> 00:37:59,960
They're all out searching for you.

556
00:38:00,640 --> 00:38:03,520
You know, Rajit is such a kind

557
00:38:04,240 --> 00:38:06,680
and sweet girl.
I want you two to become close.

558
00:38:07,840 --> 00:38:09,360
Come on, let's go.

559
00:38:09,960 --> 00:38:12,560
I knew you'd get lost.

560
00:38:51,360 --> 00:38:52,200
All set?

561
00:38:53,240 --> 00:38:54,360
Please get ready.

562
00:39:01,600 --> 00:39:04,520
Ready? One, two, three.

563
00:39:07,480 --> 00:39:09,840
One, two, three.

564
00:39:43,520 --> 00:39:45,560
That Baba outfit doesn't suit you well.

565
00:39:45,640 --> 00:39:48,160
Sorry, but I have to be honest.

566
00:39:48,240 --> 00:39:50,360
You don't look half as good as I do.

567
00:39:52,280 --> 00:39:53,720
I'll let you have your moment.

568
00:39:53,800 --> 00:39:56,120
Just don't blame me
if you can't sleep tonight.

569
00:40:06,960 --> 00:40:07,880
What is it, Rajit?

570
00:40:09,960 --> 00:40:11,880
What kind of bird is this, Uncle Ree?

571
00:40:11,960 --> 00:40:14,360
Why does it only have
one wing and one leg?

572
00:40:14,440 --> 00:40:17,360
It's called the Biyi bird.

573
00:40:17,440 --> 00:40:18,560
Biyi bird?

574
00:40:19,360 --> 00:40:22,560
What kind of bird is that?
Does it have a Thai name?

575
00:40:22,640 --> 00:40:23,560
No, there isn't.

576
00:40:23,640 --> 00:40:26,160
It's a mythical bird
from ancient folklore.

577
00:40:26,240 --> 00:40:29,560
What's the story behind it?

578
00:40:29,640 --> 00:40:31,800
Why does it only have
one wing and one leg?

579
00:40:32,400 --> 00:40:36,000
This bird is born with one wing
and one leg. It can never fly on its own,

580
00:40:36,080 --> 00:40:38,160
not until it meets its other half.

581
00:40:39,560 --> 00:40:42,200
SENG CHAROEN

582
00:40:42,280 --> 00:40:44,840
You see? Once it finds its partner,

583
00:40:44,920 --> 00:40:47,880
the two Biyi birds unite.

584
00:40:47,960 --> 00:40:50,640
Only then can they soar into the sky.

585
00:40:50,720 --> 00:40:52,280
From that moment on,

586
00:40:52,360 --> 00:40:54,240
they stay side by side,

587
00:40:54,320 --> 00:40:57,520
sharing both joy and sorrow,
for the rest of their days.

588
00:41:03,920 --> 00:41:08,360
The Biyi bird represents
an unyielding love,

589
00:41:08,440 --> 00:41:11,320
one that remains unchanged forever.

590
00:41:19,280 --> 00:41:21,040
I'll take both pieces, please.

591
00:41:21,120 --> 00:41:24,360
Certainly. Just a moment, please.

592
00:41:39,200 --> 00:41:40,440
Miss Rajit.

593
00:41:42,280 --> 00:41:43,120
Rajit.

594
00:41:43,200 --> 00:41:44,800
Where on earth have you been?

595
00:41:45,400 --> 00:41:47,720
We were about to go
to the police, you know?

596
00:41:48,320 --> 00:41:50,000
I'm so sorry.

597
00:41:50,080 --> 00:41:54,320
Oh, by the way,
where are Mr. Poj and Ms. Srichan?

598
00:41:55,480 --> 00:41:56,600
They already left.

599
00:41:56,680 --> 00:41:58,480
He bolted the second he got his wife back.

600
00:41:58,560 --> 00:42:01,000
All we got was a thank you.

601
00:42:02,440 --> 00:42:04,520
What a total waste of our time.

602
00:42:05,520 --> 00:42:07,440
But I actually agree with you, Miss Rajit,

603
00:42:07,520 --> 00:42:09,440
for helping Mr. Poj.

604
00:42:10,320 --> 00:42:12,400
I happen to know who he really is,

605
00:42:12,480 --> 00:42:15,200
and your kindness tonight

606
00:42:15,280 --> 00:42:16,800
will definitely pay off.

607
00:42:16,880 --> 00:42:20,160
Oh, I didn't think about it that way.

608
00:42:20,760 --> 00:42:22,680
I just simply wanted to help.

609
00:42:23,640 --> 00:42:26,680
So, what's the plan?
Keep walking or head home?

610
00:42:26,760 --> 00:42:29,440
We're staying, of course.
We haven't walked around at all yet.

611
00:42:30,280 --> 00:42:32,800
But I think we should probably head back.

612
00:42:33,400 --> 00:42:35,840
It's getting really late.

613
00:42:35,920 --> 00:42:39,240
Wait, so that means
we haven't spent any time together.

614
00:42:39,320 --> 00:42:40,440
Exactly.

615
00:42:40,520 --> 00:42:42,760
We spent the whole evening searching

616
00:42:42,840 --> 00:42:44,600
and got no time for ourselves.

617
00:42:44,680 --> 00:42:45,920
Should we stay just a little bit longer?

618
00:42:47,760 --> 00:42:50,520
In that case, you and Vijarn

619
00:42:50,600 --> 00:42:53,080
can stay and enjoy the festival together.

620
00:42:53,160 --> 00:42:54,680
We're going to head off now.

621
00:42:54,760 --> 00:42:56,160
Bye-bye.

622
00:42:59,480 --> 00:43:00,720
We're leaving now.

623
00:43:01,320 --> 00:43:02,840
Let's go.

624
00:43:16,920 --> 00:43:21,160
HOTEL

625
00:43:32,640 --> 00:43:36,600
<i>This bird is born with one wing</i>
<i>and one leg. It can never fly on its own,</i>

626
00:43:36,680 --> 00:43:39,200
<i>not until it meets its other half.</i>

627
00:43:39,280 --> 00:43:41,040
<i>Once it finds its partner,</i>

628
00:43:41,120 --> 00:43:44,120
<i>the two Biyi birds unite.</i>

629
00:43:44,200 --> 00:43:46,840
<i>Only then can they soar into the sky.</i>

630
00:43:46,920 --> 00:43:50,360
<i>From that moment on,</i>
<i>they stay side by side,</i>

631
00:43:50,440 --> 00:43:53,600
<i>sharing both joy and sorrow,</i>
<i>for the rest of their days.</i>

632
00:43:55,800 --> 00:43:57,080
Too sweet.

633
00:43:59,360 --> 00:44:00,800
How am I supposed to sleep?

634
00:44:12,520 --> 00:44:16,760
The Biyi bird represents
an unyielding love,

635
00:44:16,840 --> 00:44:19,560
one that remains unchanged forever.

636
00:45:20,320 --> 00:45:21,400
Uncle Ree?

637
00:45:27,640 --> 00:45:29,200
Why is he acting so sketchy?

638
00:45:43,520 --> 00:45:45,000
PHUKET HOTEL

639
00:45:53,400 --> 00:45:56,040
Tri! You finally made it.

640
00:46:06,960 --> 00:46:08,360
Going into a hotel together?

641
00:46:08,440 --> 00:46:10,360
Catching them red-handed like this,

642
00:46:10,440 --> 00:46:12,360
let's see what lie he'll come up with.

643
00:46:27,040 --> 00:46:27,960
KO HENG DIM SUM
PHUKET

644
00:46:28,040 --> 00:46:30,240
Is this your idea of a private area?

645
00:46:31,960 --> 00:46:33,280
I really think

646
00:46:33,800 --> 00:46:37,520
we could find somewhere
much more intimate.

647
00:46:39,400 --> 00:46:40,280
Stop, Sri.

648
00:46:41,280 --> 00:46:42,480
There's no need.

649
00:46:43,240 --> 00:46:44,920
I've already made up my mind.

650
00:46:45,000 --> 00:46:47,360
I will no longer let you
use Kajorn to blackmail me.

651
00:46:47,440 --> 00:46:49,240
KO HENG DIM SUM
PHUKET

652
00:46:49,320 --> 00:46:51,000
What do you mean by that?

653
00:46:51,080 --> 00:46:53,720
I'm going to ask Mr. Poj
to investigate Kajorn myself,

654
00:46:53,800 --> 00:46:55,560
in exchange for promising
to never see you again.

655
00:46:56,160 --> 00:46:57,520
He will definitely agree to it.

656
00:46:58,760 --> 00:47:01,800
How do you know

657
00:47:01,880 --> 00:47:04,280
I had Poj use his connections
to investigate?

658
00:47:05,920 --> 00:47:07,120
What a coincidence.

659
00:47:09,200 --> 00:47:11,880
I had no idea. I only found out
because you just blabbed.

660
00:47:12,720 --> 00:47:16,200
I was simply ready to risk everything
and go straight to Mr. Poj.

661
00:47:18,160 --> 00:47:21,440
From now on, you can't use this
to blackmail me anymore.

662
00:47:21,520 --> 00:47:22,600
I'm leaving.

663
00:47:22,680 --> 00:47:25,560
Oh, Tri. Please.

664
00:47:25,640 --> 00:47:29,200
Okay, fine. I'll tell you everything.

665
00:47:29,800 --> 00:47:31,720
It doesn't make a difference anyway.

666
00:47:37,000 --> 00:47:38,440
The woman Kajorn got with

667
00:47:38,520 --> 00:47:41,160
and is about to marry,
her name is Samornmit.

668
00:47:42,120 --> 00:47:45,560
<i>She's the younger sister of Yong,</i>
<i>a notorious triad boss in Yaowarat.</i>

669
00:47:45,640 --> 00:47:46,640
<i>Quite a background.</i>

670
00:47:46,720 --> 00:47:48,080
I said move! Didn't you hear?

671
00:47:48,160 --> 00:47:50,360
Move!

672
00:48:04,280 --> 00:48:06,280
But here's the best part.

673
00:48:06,360 --> 00:48:10,600
Rumor has it
that Kajorn actually knocked her up.

674
00:48:11,280 --> 00:48:14,200
And Yong is absolutely furious.

675
00:48:14,280 --> 00:48:17,280
He has no choice but to let them marry
for his sister's sake.

676
00:48:20,080 --> 00:48:23,040
If that's true, why would he
keep pestering Rajit?

677
00:48:24,080 --> 00:48:25,720
He's scored a triad leader's sister

678
00:48:25,800 --> 00:48:27,440
and has a baby on the way.

679
00:48:27,520 --> 00:48:30,720
Even if he wants
Rajit's inheritance, why risk it?

680
00:48:30,800 --> 00:48:32,160
He's been here for months now.

681
00:48:32,240 --> 00:48:33,960
Is he not worried about his future bride?

682
00:48:34,040 --> 00:48:36,280
You certainly have
a lot of questions, Tri.

683
00:48:36,360 --> 00:48:38,600
I guess you'll just have
to dig up the rest yourself.

684
00:48:41,120 --> 00:48:42,440
Though,

685
00:48:43,080 --> 00:48:45,000
you can always hire my services.

686
00:48:45,600 --> 00:48:47,560
As long as you don't
play tricks on me again.

687
00:48:59,440 --> 00:49:00,880
I actually have a way.

688
00:49:03,120 --> 00:49:04,800
If you're interested, Uncle Ree.

689
00:49:05,680 --> 00:49:06,680
Rajit…

690
00:49:16,920 --> 00:49:18,680
How could you do this to me, Uncle Ree?

691
00:49:30,240 --> 00:49:31,440
I only used a bit of cash.

692
00:49:31,520 --> 00:49:32,960
Don't be so dramatic.

693
00:49:33,040 --> 00:49:34,480
It's just a tiny amount.

694
00:49:35,080 --> 00:49:37,080
But that is our shared fund.

695
00:49:37,160 --> 00:49:39,400
You should've asked me before touching it,

696
00:49:40,000 --> 00:49:42,000
not just blowing it on whatever you want.

697
00:49:42,080 --> 00:49:44,840
Okay. Can you two please stop fighting?

698
00:49:44,920 --> 00:49:46,360
You're making such a scene

699
00:49:46,440 --> 00:49:48,760
that the whole neighborhood will hear us.

700
00:49:48,840 --> 00:49:49,640
Exactly.

701
00:49:49,720 --> 00:49:52,200
Whatever it is, just talk it out calmly.

702
00:49:53,040 --> 00:49:54,840
Let's not make a big deal out of this.

703
00:49:54,920 --> 00:49:56,080
I don't care.

704
00:49:56,160 --> 00:49:57,760
If you're going to act like this,

705
00:49:57,840 --> 00:50:00,800
let's just split the inheritance
once and for all.

706
00:50:02,800 --> 00:50:06,040
Fine. Let's split it up and cut ties.

707
00:50:06,120 --> 00:50:09,400
I'm fed up with reporting
to an immature kid like you.

708
00:50:09,480 --> 00:50:13,000
I'm just as sick
of your irresponsible behavior.

709
00:50:17,920 --> 00:50:19,760
Calm down, Rajit.

710
00:50:35,880 --> 00:50:36,920
I heard everything.

711
00:50:39,600 --> 00:50:41,160
Have you calmed down a bit?

712
00:50:43,160 --> 00:50:44,800
Seeing you like this

713
00:50:45,760 --> 00:50:47,240
breaks my heart.

714
00:50:50,200 --> 00:50:52,240
You don't have to worry about me.

715
00:50:53,040 --> 00:50:55,040
You can't stop me from worrying about you.

716
00:50:55,720 --> 00:50:58,880
You already know
that you're always on my mind.

717
00:51:01,160 --> 00:51:03,120
Thank you so much, Kajorn.

718
00:51:10,160 --> 00:51:12,920
Honestly, I never thought Mr. Thatri
would be that kind of person.

719
00:51:13,960 --> 00:51:15,760
How could he try
to steal your inheritance?

720
00:51:19,680 --> 00:51:20,720
I know.

721
00:51:22,160 --> 00:51:25,640
I don't know who I can trust
in this Som Song Saeng house anymore.

722
00:51:44,320 --> 00:51:45,320
Come in.

723
00:51:52,280 --> 00:51:54,320
You asked to see me? How can I help you?

724
00:51:55,040 --> 00:51:56,640
I'm heading to Bangkok tomorrow.

725
00:51:56,720 --> 00:51:59,000
Please inform the driver
to have the car ready for me.

726
00:52:00,160 --> 00:52:01,360
Is Miss Rajit going with you?

727
00:52:01,960 --> 00:52:04,040
No. I'm going alone.

728
00:52:04,800 --> 00:52:07,280
Does Miss Rajit know about this yet?

729
00:52:11,240 --> 00:52:13,520
Understood. I'll go tell
the driver right away.

730
00:52:14,280 --> 00:52:17,600
Thanks. And make sure
no one else finds out.

731
00:52:18,280 --> 00:52:19,120
Yes, sir.

732
00:52:19,720 --> 00:52:21,880
That's all. I need to get back to work.

733
00:52:21,960 --> 00:52:23,200
Yes, sir.

734
00:52:35,920 --> 00:52:37,440
Are you sure you want to do that?

735
00:52:37,520 --> 00:52:40,600
I don't really agree with it.
It's far too risky.

736
00:52:41,880 --> 00:52:44,240
Uncle Ree. This is what we need to do

737
00:52:44,320 --> 00:52:47,040
if we want to catch Kajorn red-handed.

738
00:52:51,960 --> 00:52:53,960
Uncle Ree sneaked off to Bangkok again?

739
00:52:54,560 --> 00:52:57,520
That's right. Mr. Thatri
insisted on keeping it a secret.

740
00:52:57,600 --> 00:52:59,360
So, I couldn't say anything.

741
00:53:01,360 --> 00:53:02,880
First he tries to steal my inheritance,

742
00:53:02,960 --> 00:53:04,560
now he's completely irresponsible.

743
00:53:13,920 --> 00:53:15,080
Rajit, what's wrong?

744
00:53:16,400 --> 00:53:17,760
It's Uncle Ree.

745
00:53:17,840 --> 00:53:19,960
He dumped all this work on me
and ran off again.

746
00:53:20,040 --> 00:53:23,400
Managing the crisis from the war
is already difficult enough,

747
00:53:23,480 --> 00:53:26,120
now I have to deal with Aunt Paetai
constantly pressuring me.

748
00:53:26,200 --> 00:53:27,920
I can't take this anymore.

749
00:53:33,160 --> 00:53:34,600
You can leave now.

750
00:53:34,680 --> 00:53:36,120
I'll take care of Rajit myself.

751
00:53:36,800 --> 00:53:37,800
Yes, sir.

752
00:53:47,960 --> 00:53:51,040
Maybe it's best if you divide the assets
and leave for a fresh start.

753
00:53:52,280 --> 00:53:54,320
If staying here
causes you this much misery…

754
00:53:55,840 --> 00:53:57,080
Do you really think so?

755
00:53:57,680 --> 00:54:01,360
I've actually wanted to flee
to Bangkok for a long time.

756
00:54:02,520 --> 00:54:04,400
But I'm just so scared of the rumors.

757
00:54:04,480 --> 00:54:07,040
Everyone will think I tricked
my Grandpa for his inheritance.

758
00:54:08,080 --> 00:54:10,960
But you're not,
so why care what they think?

759
00:54:11,040 --> 00:54:14,000
Thatri is the root of all this trouble.
Trust me.

760
00:54:14,600 --> 00:54:16,200
No one will dare say a word to you.

761
00:54:16,280 --> 00:54:17,440
That's not true.

762
00:54:17,520 --> 00:54:18,920
Every single one of my relatives

763
00:54:19,000 --> 00:54:21,080
is just waiting for a chance to crush me.

764
00:54:21,160 --> 00:54:24,960
Those relatives don't matter at all.
Why waste your energy on them?

765
00:54:25,040 --> 00:54:29,520
As long as you and I know what's real,

766
00:54:29,600 --> 00:54:30,680
that's more than enough.

767
00:54:40,800 --> 00:54:42,800
Thank you so much, Kajorn.

768
00:54:44,080 --> 00:54:46,200
You've been incredibly kind to me.

769
00:54:52,680 --> 00:54:54,280
Come to Bangkok with me.

770
00:54:55,640 --> 00:54:58,680
As for the assets, we can leave Vijarn
to handle all the details.

771
00:55:07,200 --> 00:55:08,480
Alright.

772
00:55:17,440 --> 00:55:19,000
Please stop Miss Rajit.

773
00:55:19,080 --> 00:55:21,480
- She's being fooled right into his trap.
- Yes.

774
00:55:22,480 --> 00:55:23,680
Miss Rajit.

775
00:55:23,760 --> 00:55:27,480
Auntie Jiam told me
that you are really moving to Bangkok

776
00:55:27,560 --> 00:55:29,920
while the inheritance is being settled?

777
00:55:30,840 --> 00:55:32,080
Yes.

778
00:55:32,160 --> 00:55:34,800
I'm completely sick
and tired of this place.

779
00:55:34,880 --> 00:55:37,120
I'm going to rebuild my life over there.

780
00:55:37,920 --> 00:55:40,680
I'll leave the inheritance matters
in your hands, Mr. Vijarn.

781
00:55:43,080 --> 00:55:44,680
Let me carry that suitcase for you.

782
00:55:46,040 --> 00:55:47,000
Thank you.

783
00:55:49,200 --> 00:55:51,240
Miss Rajit, please reconsider this.

784
00:55:51,840 --> 00:55:53,320
If you go through with this,

785
00:55:53,400 --> 00:55:55,080
you have absolutely nothing to gain.

786
00:55:55,640 --> 00:55:57,920
I've already made up my mind, Mr. Vijarn.

787
00:55:58,000 --> 00:56:00,160
You don't need to worry about me.

788
00:56:00,240 --> 00:56:02,440
Once the inheritance matters
are fully settled,

789
00:56:03,160 --> 00:56:05,200
I will come back to claim it myself.

790
00:56:06,520 --> 00:56:07,360
But if you leave--

791
00:56:07,440 --> 00:56:09,040
No more buts, Mr. Vijarn.

792
00:56:09,120 --> 00:56:10,960
Rajit has already made her choice.

793
00:56:11,760 --> 00:56:13,240
Why are you holding her back?

794
00:56:15,200 --> 00:56:18,320
Rajit, right this way.

795
00:56:22,120 --> 00:56:23,640
I'm sorry, Mr. Vijarn.

796
00:56:51,000 --> 00:56:52,440
Kajorn, what are you doing?

797
00:56:52,520 --> 00:56:53,960
You're finally mine.

798
00:56:54,720 --> 00:56:56,240
I'm here to talk to you about Kajorn.

799
00:56:56,320 --> 00:56:58,480
This is the very first time we've met.

800
00:56:58,560 --> 00:57:01,080
Why should I share stories
about my lover with you?

801
00:57:01,160 --> 00:57:02,200
So you found me here

802
00:57:02,280 --> 00:57:04,800
because you can't handle
my crazy family in Phuket, huh?

803
00:57:04,880 --> 00:57:06,600
You're from Phuket, Uncle?

804
00:57:07,280 --> 00:57:09,040
I am from Phuket as well.

805
00:57:10,880 --> 00:57:12,280
If I could turn back time…

806
00:57:12,360 --> 00:57:14,200
What would you want to change, Uncle Ree?

807
00:57:14,280 --> 00:57:15,840
I wouldn't want to change a thing.

808
00:57:15,920 --> 00:57:17,920
Are you talking about the fortune?

809
00:57:18,640 --> 00:57:20,080
To be right by my fortune.

810
00:57:52,400 --> 00:57:54,400
Subtitle translation by:
Khathathong Thongtumlueng
